The paper deals with image classification using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a novel training strategy for the proposed model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of hierarchical classification and prior knowledge also suggests the possibility of using neural networks for natural language processing tasks, such as text classification (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves the optimization of neural network parameters, which is a common topic in neural engineering (cs.NE).
